At least 77 people were arrested for various offences during Operation Paseka in North West, the provincial police said on Monday. The suspects were arrested for contact crimes, drugs, as well as liquor related crimes through various operations that were executed to ensure safety on national roads, residential areas and places where people gathered in large numbers, said Brigadier Sabata Mokgwabone. He said the operation was conducted between Thursday and Monday. As part of the operations, the police together with other law enforcement agencies managed to issue 198 road traffic and liquor related offences fines. A firearm, two vehicles, drugs, knives and various electrical appliances were confiscated during the operations. African News Agency For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.